<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900905-0012</DOCNO><DOCID>900905-0012.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- J.P. Morgan andamp; Co.:   Sumitomo Life to Refinance   Company's London Offices</HL><DATE>09/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   JPM J.SLI</CO><IN>MAJOR MONEY CENTER BANKS (BAN)BANKS (BNK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   J.P. Morgan andamp; Co. said it arranged for a $416 millionrefinancing of its London office complex through SumitomoLife Insurance Co. of Japan.   The New York-based bank holding company said it hadentered into an agreement with Sumitomo Life that would givethe Japanese insurance company a 52.5% stake on a structuredbasis of Morgan Place, the office complex it is building at60 Victoria Embankment.</LP><TEXT>   Under terms of the agreement, J.P. Morgan would receive a25-year lease with renewal options for 50 years. The companysaid no immediate gain would be realized from the transactionand that the benefits would be realized over the 25-year lifeof the lease.</TEXT></DOC>